1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the characterization of achievable rate regions, which is a fundamental concept in information theory. 
2. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper focuses on the single-antenna Z interference channel, which is a communication channel. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the transmission of complex Gaussian signals, which is a common technique in multimedia communication. 
4. cs.SI (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses optimal strategies and properties of the Pareto boundary, which are related to control and optimization. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with interference channels, which are a key concept in networking and internet architecture.
